**Visual Studio 16.8.2**: 

**Steps to Reproduce**:

1: Define the following method with a single nullable array parameter.
```
/// <summary>
/// Test Documentation
/// </summary>
/// <param name="param1">This is param 1.</param>
public static void BaseMethod(string[]? param1) { }
```
2: Define two methods that inherit the documentation, one with a nullable string array parameter and one with an array of nullable string parameter (it's hard to notice but the ? operator is on the other side of the array declaration in `inheritdoc`).
```
/// <inheritdoc cref="BaseMethod(string[]?)"/>
public static void Test1(string[]? param1) { }

/// <inheritdoc cref="BaseMethod(string?[])"/>
public static void Test2(string[]? param1) { }
```

**Expected Behavior**:
`Test1` Should display the docs of `BaseMethod`
`Test2` *inheritdoc* has the NRT attribute on the wrong side of the array so should not match the `BaseMethod` and should throw compiler error CS1584 (syntactically incorrect cref attribute)

**Actual Behavior**:
`Test1` fails to show the `BaseMethod` documentation and throws compiler error CS1584
`Test2` shows the docs of `BaseMethod` even though the `inheritdoc` signature does *not* match.

